    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my realtor just mentioned something about an escrow account for the closing and i'm kinda confused. what exactly is escrow and why do i need it for the house purchase?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Escrow is essentially a neutral third party that holds funds and documents until all conditions of your real estate transaction are met. It ensures that both the buyer and seller are protected by preventing any single party from getting paid or transferring title until the other side has fulfilled their obligations. You need it because it manages the flow of money and paperwork safely, so you don't hand over your down payment directly to the seller or the lender before everything is verified. Without this step, you'd be at significant risk of losing your money or being held hostage by the seller, which is why every reputable real estate agent uses escrow. You can think of it as a safe vault that only releases items when a specific checklist is complete.",
