    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. so is the escrow company basically just acting like a middleman or a guard for the money while everything's being finalized? like they're just sitting there holding onto it until the very end?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, that's exactly right! The escrow company acts as a neutral middleman and a guardian of the funds, holding the money and documents securely until every single condition of your contract is satisfied. They don't just sit passively; they actively verify that the loan is approved, the title is clear, and all inspections are passed before releasing anything to either party. Think of them as the ultimate referee in a game of checkers, making sure no piece moves until the rules have been strictly followed. This careful oversight is what prevents fraud and ensures a smooth transaction for everyone involved.",
